description: The `synthetic.call_logs` table represents a record of communication activities, capturing details of each call such as the subject, type, result, and duration. It stores metadata about the call's timing and associations with other entities, indicated by `related_to_type` and `related_to_id`, without any explicit foreign key relationships to other tables. Primarily serving as a log for tracking interactions, this table plays a crucial role in monitoring communication patterns and outcomes within the specified context.

columns.name: call_id
columns.description: This column represents a unique identifier for each individual call record within the call logs table. It ensures that each call entry can be distinctly referenced and tracked.

columns.name: subject
columns.description: This column contains narrative or descriptive entries which may represent summaries or overviews related to individual call logs. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: call_result
columns.description: This column captures a summary or outcome of phone interactions, possibly reflecting topics, actions, or results related to various fields like economy, work, science, and agreements. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: call_date
columns.description: This column records the date and time when each call occurred, capturing details of individual call logs. It provides chronological context for the call activities in the dataset.

columns.name: duration_minutes
columns.description: This column represents the length of time, measured in minutes, for individual call logs within the database. The values indicate varying durations of calls, suggesting a record of call activity possibly for billing or usage analysis purposes.

columns.name: description
columns.description: This column appears to contain miscellaneous narrative or commentary entries that are part of call logs, detailing aspects of interactions or transactions. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: related_to_id
columns.description: This column likely represents an identifier linking related records within a system, such as connections between different calls or entries. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: owner_id
columns.description: This column likely represents the unique identifiers for individuals or entities who own or are associated with specific call records in the call logs. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: created_at
columns.description: This column records the date and time when each call log entry was created, reflecting the moment these entries were generated in the system. Its purpose is to track the timestamp of call log creation for historical or operational analysis.

columns.name: updated_at
columns.description: This column represents the date and time when a record in the call logs table was last updated. Typically, it automatically initializes or updates to the current timestamp when changes occur in the table.

indexes.index_definition: CREATE UNIQUE INDEX call_logs_pkey ON synthetic.call_logs USING btree (call_id)
